Not parallel universes with different histories. Here's the reframe —

Every person who becomes awakened fractured at a specific moment. A moment where they almost went a completely different direction — and some version of them did. The alternate timeline isn't a separate universe running alongside ours. It's more like — the road not taken became load-bearing. It's still happening, underneath, and the awakened can sometimes feel the weight of their other paths pressing up through the floor of their current life.

Her timeline fractured differently than his. Same person, same core — but her fracture point came earlier, under different pressure, and so she woke up faster and harder and lonelier. When they eventually meet, they will recognize each other not romantically first — but with the specific vertigo of someone who almost was you.

